<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1222,1823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1546,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blainville" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[328,451,1546,1571]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinometridae" genus="Echinostrephus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="molaris">
<emphasis box="[328,345,1548,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[366,451,1546,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">molaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the other echinometrid species recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[1312,1432,1546,1571]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[151,581,1582,1607]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinometridae" genus="Colobocentrotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="atratus" subGenus="Podophora">
<emphasis box="[151,337,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Colobocentrotus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[356,482,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Podophora</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[502,581,1583,1606]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[599,743,1582,1607]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinometridae" genus="Echinometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[599,743,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Echinometra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[868,1183,1582,1607]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinometridae" genus="Heterocentrotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="mamillatus">
<emphasis box="[868,1183,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Heterocentrotus mamillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in having three pore pairs in the pore arcs of the ambulacra and a unique lateral aspect, with the ambitus located high on the test and the aboral side distinctly flattened. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blainville" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[504,620,1654,1679]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinometridae" genus="Echinostrephus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="molaris">
<emphasis box="[504,620,1654,1679]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">E. molaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has a small, circular test with a flattened, broad aboral side. Unique to the genus, the longest spines project vertically in an aboral tuft, whereas the spines on the ambitus and oral surface are extremely short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1222,1823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
This species was first recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[645,761,1762,1787]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Doderlein, L." box="[813,1013,1762,1787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" pagination="821 - 846" refId="ref9470" refString="Doderlein, L. (1888) Echinodermen von Ceylon. Bericht uber die von den Herren D res Sarasin gesammelten Asteroidea, Ophiuroidea und Echinoidea. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere, 3, 821 - 846. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 1933" type="journal article" year="1888">Döderlein (1888)</bibRefCitation>
under the incorrectly formed name “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blainville" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[163,421,1798,1823]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinometridae" genus="Echinostrephus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="molare">
<emphasis box="[163,421,1798,1823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Echinostrephus molare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”.
</paragraph>
